76561198069159152,Recommended,458060,31552736,Posted: 4 May,all,wrb41977,"This is a very, very short visual novel. There are five endings, most of which aren't that great. Julia Drusilla, sister of Gaius Julius Caesar Augustus Germanicus, better known as Caligula. While the game builds on rumors that she and her brother were lovers, there is really no historical evidence of such (in fact, most of the rumors were made up later to discredit Caligula). What is true, is that upon her death in 38 AD, Caligula had her deified (something which probably lead to some of the rumors of her being a ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥). Also true is when Caligula fell ill in 37 AD, he named her as his heir (to continue the line of Julius Caesar, from whom both were descended). Side note: That illness may well have done some mental damage which lead to the later insanity from which he is said to have suffered.Okay, I have probably above given you more historical information than is in this entire game. No matter...The game itself is a bit of fluff. If you approach it as such, you might even enjoy it. If, on the other hand, you approach it for historical accuracy... go elsewhere."
